<LP>
   CALDOR Inc., Norwalk, Conn., said it completed $300
million in new permanent financing arrangements to help
retire a $460 million bridge loan obtained in connection with
its management buy-out in November 1989. It also arranged up
to $235 million in new working capital from Citibank,
Chemical Bank and Security Pacific Business Inc.
